This package contains the classes for handling the cabling configuration of
the MDT detector. The cabling service requires the AMDB package for accessing
the geometry data.


Basic Components:

MDTGeometry    : singleton class handling the data structures which hold the
                 geometric position of the RPC strips. It contains also the
                 map between the CSM modules and the ReadOut Tower.

MDTgeoemtrySvc : interface class implementing the access to the RPCGeometry
                 class as an ATHENA service.

CSMid          : class modelling the CSM module related to an MDT chamber.
 
MRODscheme     : class modelling the MROD wich receives input from up to 8 CSM

ReadOutTower   : class modelling the Readout Towers along eta. It collect the
                 MROD acquiring data from the same eta slice.


Use and configuration in ATHENA:

    * Load and use the required DLL module with the following command lines:

       ApplicationMgr.DLLs += { "MDTcabling" , "AmdbsimrecAthena"};
       ApplicationMgr.ExtSvc += { "AmdbsimrecAthenaSvc", "MDTcablingSvc" };

    * The geometry database amdb_simrec.data must be accessible from the run
      directory.

    * The mrod database ROBmap.data must be accessible from the run directory. 
      A copy of that file can be found into the share directory.

    * Configuration parameters:

      MapFlag   [false]  output on std device the geometry parameters
      GeoFlag   [false]  output on std device the MDT geometry data
      CheFlag   [false]  output on std device the MDT chamber readout schema
      DumpFlag  [false]  flag for dumping out the  geometry parameters
      ReadFlag  [false]  flag for reading the geometry parameters from a file
                         instead of AMDB
      GEOfile   ["GEOmap.data"] file containing the dump of the geometry
      RODfile   ["RODmap.data"] file conatining the map of CSM into MDRO 
